{"name": "duckdb-appender", "metadata": {"name": "duckdb-appender", "version": "0.2.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["duckdb"], "summary": "A DuckDB appender for Python", "upload_time": 1732097791}, "documentation": ["# DuckDB PyAppender\n\nA DuckDB appender for Python.\n\n## Usage\n\n```py\nconn = duckdb.connect()\n\nappender = Appender(conn, schema=\"main\", table=\"users\")\nappender.append_row([1, \"John\"])\nappender.append_row([2, \"Doe\"])\nappender.close()\n\n# Can also use it with context manager:\nwith Appender(conn, schema=\"main\", table=\"users\") as appender:\n  appender.append_row([3, \"foo\"])\n```\n\nSee more in the `/examles` folder.\n\n## Why use this\n\n- Much faster than simple INSERT statements.\n- Versus storing data in a pandas DataFrame and load into DuckDB: while pandas loads the entire dataset into memory, this appender uses SQLite as a buffer that regularly flush itself (every 204,800 rows, similar to the official C++ appender)\n  - This prevents memory overload on large data aggregation.\n  - A little bit of crash protection - since it commits data every 204,800 rows, you'll preserve most of your progress if something goes wrong.\n\n## Local development\n\nThis repo uses [uv](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv) to manage dependencies and\nvirtual environment. Dependencies are written in `pyproject.toml`, so other\ntools supporting it can be used as well.\n\n### Run test\n\nThis repo use [pytest](https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/). To run tests within an uv environment, run:\n\n```bash\nuv run pytest\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "appender.errors", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "appender.errors.TableNotFoundError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Cannot find the table in DuckDB"]}, {"name": "appender.errors.ColumnCountError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [{"name": "appender.errors.ColumnCountError.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "expected", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "actual", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "appender.errors.AppendAfterCloseError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Cannot append after having closed the appender"]}, {"name": "appender.errors.AppenderDoubleCloseError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The appender is already closed"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "appender", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "appender.AppendAfterCloseError", "xref": {"fqname": "appender.errors.AppendAfterCloseError", "project": null}}, {"name": "appender.Appender", "xref": {"fqname": "appender.appender.Appender", "project": null}}, {"name": "appender.AppenderDoubleCloseError", "xref": {"fqname": "appender.errors.AppenderDoubleCloseError", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "appender.appender", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "appender.appender._convert_duckdb_to_sqlite_schema", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "schema", "type": {"name": "TableSchema", "xref": {"fqname": "appender.appender.TableSchema", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables"